def: The doctrine or system of those who deduce their religiousopinions from reason or the understanding, as distinct from, oropposed to, revelation.
Of or relating to stagnation of the blood.

Any one of the abdominal appendages of a crustacean, especiallyone of the posterior ones, which are often larger than the rest, anddifferent in structure, and are used chiefly in locomotion. SeeIllust. of Crustacea, and Stomapoda.
To sustain; to support. [Obs.] "His massy spear upstayed."Milton.
Having many forms, shapes, or appearances.A plastic and multiform unit. Hare.
Mangy; scabby; hence, mean; paltry; troublesome. [Written alsoroinish.] [Obs.] "The roynish clown." Shak.
Situated under the periosteum. Subperiosteal operation (Surg.),a removal of bone effected without taking away the periosteum.
